09/06/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Over 60 experts took part in a meeting Thursday (8 June) in Skopje to co-ordinate activities against human trafficking in Kosovo and Macedonia.
Invitations to the event, organised by the International Organisation for Migration, were sent to all NGOs dealing with the issue.
The forum is aimed at boosting cross-border co-operation in combating human trafficking through training, public awareness and prevention programmes.
(Albanian News - 09/06/06;
Makfax - 08/06/06)
